{
  "abstract": "Agriculture is a critical sector of the Indian economy. Though agriculture's contribution to the overall Gross Domestic Product (GDP) of the country has fallen from about 30% in 1990-91 to <15 % in 2011-12, agriculture yet forms the backbone of development. Achieving an 8-9 % rate of growth in overall GDP would help in poverty reduction and in providing food and nutritional security to all Indians, only when agricultural growth accelerates....",
